Dear Parents,
We appreciate your patience as we make preparations for the coming school year. This week your child‚Äôs homeroom

post_text: Farmington School District's Ready to Learn Committee has released information to Students, Staff, and Parents/Guardians regarding the 2020-2021 School year. Superintendent Jon Laffoon released a letter this afternoon that outlines the procedures and protocols that will be in place for the coming school year regarding COVID-19, Blended Learning and Virtual Learning. The district's procedures are based on the Arkansas Ready for Learning model, which is set forth by the Division of Elementary and Secondary Education (DESE). The full letter with procedures & protocols can be read here: https://bit.ly/3fx6FgT

Parents, please set up your athletes on Dragonfly Max to ensure eligibility. Signing up is easy!

Download the DragonFly MAX app from the App Store or Google Play.
Tap ‚ÄòGet Started‚Äô and ‚ÄòSign Up for Free‚Äô then follow the prompts to create your Parent account with your own email address.
Note: please do not create an account with your child‚Äôs name or
contact information ‚Äî you will get the chance to add your child soon!
Verify your account with the verification ID sent to your email address.
Tap ‚ÄòConnect to your school‚Äô to select ‚ÄòParent‚Äô as your role and search for your child‚Äôs school.
After selecting your child‚Äôs school, tap ‚ÄòJoin‚Äô to request access. An administrator at your school will approve your request.
Tap ‚ÄòSet up your children‚Äô and follow the prompts to add your kid(s) and fill out their participation forms.

You can also go to https://www.dragonflymax.com/ and sign up using your computer!

post_text: Free wifi internet is available at all Farmington Schools Parking lots. However, the east lot of the Jr. High has extra capacity and coverage. In addition, PGTELCO has free wifi at the Farmington First Baptist Church parking lot on Rheas Mill Rd. OzarksGoGo has also setup free wifi access points at the Weddington Baptist Church and the Savoy Community Center building. Any students who need a Chromebook can continue to check them out through their school office. We appreciate PGTelco and OzarksGo for their work in getting this service available to the community at no charge!

post_text:
If your student needs a meal, but you are unable to pick it up, please fill out the form below or call 479-266-1814 by 6pm tonight. Please be sure to leave a list of all students under the age of 18 in the household and your address. We will deliver meals between 9am and 10:30am tomorrow. We can only deliver to students who live in the district and the students must be present to accept the meal at delivery. Meals will still be available for pickup at the Jr High during that same 9am to 10:30am time slot.

Link to form: https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSfEBBNyytkKPeh0TnXxigxfmba5Hc3qiHJCekiocO4kPDcKmA/viewform

post_text: We are continuing to monitor the situation with COVID-19. There are still no reported cases in our school or community. However, we are implementing temporary school trip travel restrictions as a precautionary measure. There will be no school trips out of state and all trips will be limited to Benton and Washington counties only. Also, there is no news regarding any changes to the Girls State Championship tomorrow night. At this point, that game is still on and open to the public. If there are any changes, we will be sure to update you as soon as possible.

It‚Äôs that time of Summer when the kids are getting restless and need to burn off some energy. We‚Äôve got you covered with a wide selection of kids sports camps in July.

-Football Kids Camp: July 10th and 11th from 5:30 pm to 7:00 pm at Allen Holland Field. Grades 2-7. Registration begins at 4:30 pm. $50 per camper or $80 for siblings.

-Cardinal Basketball Academy: July 15-17 from 8:30 am to 11:30 for 6th-9th graders at Massey Gym and 12:30 pm to 3:30 pm for 1st - 5th grade at the Middle School Gym.

-ELITE Performance Speed & Strength Camp: July 8th, 9th, 18th, 19th, 22nd, 24th, 25th and 29th for boys and girls grades 6th-12th grades at Cardinal Arena.

Please visit www.farmcards.org for more information and registration options for all the camps.

post_text: The annual Farmington Back to School Bonanza will be Thursday, August 1st, from 4:30 to 7pm at Farmington United Methodist Church. 355 Southwinds Drive, Farmington, AR. This event is for students entering Kindergarten through 12th grades. Participants will receive tennis shoes, haircuts, backpacks, socks, underwear, vision and dental screenings and kindergarten school physicals. All our welcome, but the child must be present to receive items. For more information or to volunteer call (479)267-3180 or (479) 530-6412.

This award is determined by the audience applause, so it‚Äôs important for you to come out and help cheer on your favorite act to victory!

Farmington Booster Club
January 31, 2019 at 8:28 PM ¬∑

Job Opportunity:

The Booster Club is proud to join forces with the City of Farmington. We will be running the concession stand at the City baseball and softball fields. Mayor Penn has decided to keep the money local!

We will be a hiring local person to be a concession stand manager. Approx $75 per day - minimal hours. If you or someone you know is interested please have them email us at:

boosterclub@farmcards.org

Duties:
Schedule weekly/daily
Oversee groups working
Stocking stand
Opening and sometimes closing
Some weekends for tournaments
Trips to Sams
Daily deposits/withdrawals
Available from March-July

We fill this position is best suited for someone that wants to be heavily involved with Farmington and our great organizations that will be assisting. If you know someone that is interested or would like to promote this feel free to share/like.
